.TH SINGINE-SMTP 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-smtp \- test SMTP connectivity and send mail
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine smtp
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B smtp
command tests SMTP connectivity or sends a test message using explicit CLI
flags, environment variables, or IdP-derived configuration.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B test
Connect, issue EHLO, negotiate TLS when available, and optionally authenticate.
.TP
.B send
Send a test message, defaulting to self when sender information is available.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Resolution order is: CLI flags, environment variables, IdP properties, then
1Password references when configured.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine smtp test --host smtp.example.org --port 587 --user you@example.org
singine smtp send --to you@example.org --subject "singine test" --body "hello"
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1)
